<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1180.107551.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Varicus prometheus sp. nov. holotype, UW 158119, 30.5 mm SL, female, prior to preservation (top two photos) and preserved (bottom). Photos by Luke Tornabene." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/908647" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1180.107551.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Vertebral skeleton and anal-fin pterygiophores of Varicus prometheus sp. nov. Yellow numbers are the number of vertebrae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/908648" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1180.107551.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Sensory papillae pattern for Varicus prometheus. Labels for papillae rows follow Sanzo (1911) as modified by Tornabene et al. (2016 b). Photo by L. Tornabene." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/908649" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1180.107551.figure5>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Live or fresh coloration of Varicus species (coloration unknown for V. benthonis and V. bucca) A V. adamsi, photo by L. Tornabene B V. cephalocellatus, photo by B. Brown C V. decorum, photo by B. Brown D V. lacerta, photo by C. Baldwin E V. marilynae, illustration by R. G. Gilmore F V. veliguttatus, photo by C. Baldwin G V. nigritus, illustration by R. G. Gilmor H V. vespa, photo by the crew of the R / V BELLOWS." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/908650" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

